ociate\naffective meaning to words based on surface patterns, but also based on\nsimilarities to existing words (\"juy\" to \"joy\", or \"flike\" to \"like\").\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Feb 2022 14:48:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Apr 2022 12:35:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 20 Apr 2022 15:45:12 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 16 May 2022 11:22:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-17"}
